Interface IInAppMessageViewWrapper

    public interface IInAppMessageViewWrapper

    • Method Detail

      • open

        void open(android.app.Activity activity)
        Opens an IInAppMessage on the Activity. As a result of this call, it is expected that an IInAppMessage is visible and interactable by the user. Note that this method is expected to be called on the main UI thread and should run synchronously.

      • close

        void close()
        Closes an IInAppMessage. As a result of this call, it is expected that an IInAppMessage is no longer visible and not interactable by the user. Note that this method is expected to be called on the main UI thread and should run synchronously.

      • getInAppMessageView

        android.view.View getInAppMessageView()
        Returns:
        The View representing the IInAppMessage that is visible to the user.

      • getInAppMessage

        IInAppMessage getInAppMessage()
        Returns:
        The IInAppMessage being wrapped.

      • getIsAnimatingClose

        boolean getIsAnimatingClose()
        Returns:
        Whether the IInAppMessage view is currently in the process of its close animation.
